ificant events of the era—the success of the Haitian slave revolution, Napoleon’s decision to sell the Louisiana Territory, a change in the geopolitical situation of the new United States—and spins a riveting tale of unintended consequences and the legacy of slavery that will not die.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAbolitionistszGreat BritainvBiography. 0aAntislavery movements -- Great Britain -- History -- 18th century. 0aAntislavery movementszGreat BritainxHistoryy18th century. 0aEpidemics -- History -- 18th century. 0aEpidemicsxHistoryy18th century. 0aHankey (Ship : 1784). 0aYellow fever -- Caribbean Area -- History -- 18th century. 0aYellow fever -- Guinea-Bissau -- Bolama Island -- History -- 18th century. 0aYellow fever -- United States -- History -- 18th century. 0aYellow feverzCaribbean AreaxHistoryy18th century. 0aYellow feverzGuinea-BissauzBolama IslandxHistoryy18th century. 0aYellow feverzUnited StatesxHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 18th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019923940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300199239423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300199239/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles